  <!-- ── Technology Reference ──────────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="ref-grid" style="grid-template-columns:1fr">
  <div class="ref-section" id="tech">
    <div class="window-wrap fade-up">
      <div class="window-bar">
        <span class="window-dot dot-red"></span><span class="window-dot dot-yellow"></span><span class="window-dot dot-green"></span>
        <span style="margin-left:10px;font-size:12px;color:var(--muted)">Technology Reference</span>
      </div>
      <div class="window-body" style="padding:20px">

        <div class="tech-group-label">Application layer</div>
        <div class="tech-grid">
          <div class="tech-card">
            <div class="tech-card-head"><span class="tech-card-name">Node.js</span><span class="tech-card-ver">v24 LTS</span></div>
            <div class="tech-card-role">Server runtime. Uses native ESM modules (<code>type:"module"</code>), native <code>fetch</code>, and async/await throughout. No Babel or transpilation.</div>
            <code class="tech-card-file">tools/atlas-webapp/package.json</code>
          </div>
          <div class="tech-card">
            <div class="tech-card-head"><span class="tech-card-name">Express</span><span class="tech-card-ver">4.x</span></div>
            <div class="tech-card-role">HTTP server framework. Route handlers read JSON data files and render EJS templates. No middleware for auth — all routes are public localhost-only.</div>
            <code class="tech-card-file">tools/atlas-webapp/server.js</code>
          </div>
          <div class="tech-card">
            <div class="tech-card-head"><span class="tech-card-name">EJS</span><span class="tech-card-ver">3.x</span></div>
            <div class="tech-card-role">Server-side HTML templating. Partials: <code>head</code>, <code>nav</code>, <code>footer</code>. <code>NODE_ENV=production</code> enables compiled template cache — restart container after .ejs edits.</div>
            <code class="tech-card-file">tools/atlas-webapp/views/</code>
          </div>
          <div class="tech-card">
            <div class="tech-card-head"><span class="tech-card-name">Chart.js</span><span class="tech-card-ver">4.x CDN</span></div>
            <div class="tech-card-role">Browser-side charting for price history, health trends, and budget graphs. Loaded from CDN only on pages that need it (<code>includeCharts: true</code> in head partial).</div>
            <code class="tech-card-file">views/partials/head.ejs</code>
          </div>
          <div class="tech-card">
            <div class="tech-card-head"><span class="tech-card-name">FullCalendar</span><span class="tech-card-ver">6.x CDN</span></div>
            <div class="tech-card-role">Calendar page UI. Fetches events from <code>/api/calendar/events</code> as JSON. Reads from local <code>data/organizer/calendar-events.json</code> written by calendar-agent.</div>
            <code class="tech-card-file">views/calendar.ejs</code>
          </div>
          <div class="tech-card">
            <div class="tech-card-head"><span class="tech-card-name">ESLint</span><span class="tech-card-ver">10.x</span></div>
            <div class="tech-card-role">JS linting with flat config. Runs via <code>npm run lint</code>. ESM-aware, no legacy .eslintrc files. Enforced before every deploy.</div>
            <code class="tech-card-file">tools/atlas-webapp/eslint.config.js</code>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tech-group-label">Data &amp; scraping</div>
        <div class="tech-grid">
          <div class="tech-card">
            <div class="tech-card-head"><span class="tech-card-name">JSON flat files</span><span class="tech-card-ver">no DB</span></div>
            <div class="tech-card-role">All persistence uses human-readable JSON. No SQL, no ORM. Writes are atomic file replacements. Git-friendly. Data directory bind-mounted as <code>/atlas-data</code>.</div>
            <code class="tech-card-file">data/</code>
          </div>
          <div class="tech-card">
            <div class="tech-card-head"><span class="tech-card-name">Cheerio</span><span class="tech-card-ver">1.x</span></div>
            <div class="tech-card-role">jQuery-like HTML parsing for the price scraper CLI. Each store has its own scraper that selects price elements by CSS selector. Selector breaks when stores update their HTML.</div>
            <code class="tech-card-file">tools/price-tracker/scrapers/</code>
          </div>
          <div class="tech-card">
            <div class="tech-card-head"><span class="tech-card-name">prom-client</span><span class="tech-card-ver">15.x</span></div>
            <div class="tech-card-role">Prometheus metrics client. Exposes HTTP request counters, latency histograms, and a custom product count gauge at <code>/metrics</code>. Scraped by Prometheus every 15 s.</div>
            <code class="tech-card-file">tools/atlas-webapp/server.js</code>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tech-group-label">Infrastructure</div>
        <div class="tech-grid">
          <div class="tech-card">
            <div class="tech-card-head"><span class="tech-card-name">Docker Engine</span><span class="tech-card-ver">24.0.3</span></div>
            <div class="tech-card-role">Container runtime running natively inside WSL2 via systemd. No Docker Desktop. All containers share bridge network <code>atlas_net</code>. Volumes are Windows filesystem bind mounts.</div>
            <code class="tech-card-file">docker-compose.yml</code>
          </div>
          <div class="tech-card">
            <div class="tech-card-head"><span class="tech-card-name">Docker Compose</span><span class="tech-card-ver">v2.19.1</span></div>
            <div class="tech-card-role">Multi-container orchestration. 4 services: webapp, prometheus, grafana, nginx. Use <code>--force-recreate</code> after changing env vars or volume mounts — <code>restart</code> alone doesn't re-apply them.</div>
            <code class="tech-card-file">docker-compose.yml</code>
          </div>
          <div class="tech-card">
            <div class="tech-card-head"><span class="tech-card-name">WSL2</span><span class="tech-card-ver">Ubuntu-22.04</span></div>
            <div class="tech-card-role">Linux subsystem with full systemd support. Docker, Prometheus, and Grafana run inside WSL2. All <code>docker</code> / <code>docker compose</code> commands must be prefixed with <code>wsl -d Ubuntu-22.04</code>.</div>
            <code class="tech-card-file">/etc/wsl.conf</code>
          </div>
          <div class="tech-card">
            <div class="tech-card-head"><span class="tech-card-name">nginx</span><span class="tech-card-ver">alpine</span></div>
            <div class="tech-card-role">Reverse proxy container included for future TLS termination and multi-service routing. Currently bypassed — webapp is accessed directly on port 3456.</div>
            <code class="tech-card-file">config/nginx/</code>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tech-group-label">Observability</div>
        <div class="tech-grid">
          <div class="tech-card">
            <div class="tech-card-head"><span class="tech-card-name">Prometheus</span><span class="tech-card-ver">latest</span></div>
            <div class="tech-card-role">Pull-based metrics collection. Scrapes <code>atlas-webapp:3456/metrics</code> on a 15 s interval. Stores time-series data locally. Accessible at <code>localhost:9090</code>.</div>
            <code class="tech-card-file">config/prometheus.yml</code>
          </div>
          <div class="tech-card">
            <div class="tech-card-head"><span class="tech-card-name">Grafana</span><span class="tech-card-ver">latest</span></div>
            <div class="tech-card-role">Dashboard visualisation. Datasource is Prometheus. Dashboards provisioned automatically from config files on container start. Access at <code>localhost:3000</code>.</div>
            <code class="tech-card-file">config/grafana/</code>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tech-group-label">AI &amp; automation</div>
        <div class="tech-grid">
          <div class="tech-card">
            <div class="tech-card-head"><span class="tech-card-name">Claude Code</span><span class="tech-card-ver">CLI / SDK</span></div>
            <div class="tech-card-role">Anthropic's official CLI and agent SDK. Reads agent definitions from <code>.claude/agents/</code>, runs slash commands from <code>.claude/commands/</code>, executes hooks from <code>.claude/settings.json</code>.</div>
            <code class="tech-card-file">.claude/</code>
          </div>
          <div class="tech-card">
            <div class="tech-card-head"><span class="tech-card-name">Claude API</span><span class="tech-card-ver">Anthropic</span></div>
            <div class="tech-card-role">Three tiers: <code>opus-4-7</code> for orchestration, <code>sonnet-4-6</code> for balanced work, <code>haiku-4-5</code> for quick classification. API key in <code>.env</code>, never committed.</div>
            <code class="tech-card-file">config/atlas.yaml</code>
          </div>
          <div class="tech-card">
            <div class="tech-card-head"><span class="tech-card-name">MCP</span><span class="tech-card-ver">stdio servers</span></div>
            <div class="tech-card-role">Model Context Protocol — enables Claude Code to call Google Calendar and Gmail. Servers are launched on demand by Claude Code (not always running). OAuth2 auth flow on first use.</div>
            <code class="tech-card-file">.mcp.json</code>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── Troubleshooting ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="ref-grid" style="grid-template-columns:1fr">
  <div class="ref-section" id="troubleshooting">
    <div class="window-wrap fade-up">
      <div class="window-bar">
        <span class="window-dot dot-red"></span><span class="window-dot dot-yellow"></span><span class="window-dot dot-green"></span>
        <span style="margin-left:10px;font-size:12px;color:var(--muted)">Troubleshooting</span>
      </div>
      <div class="window-body" style="padding:20px">
        <div class="trouble-list">

          <details class="trouble">
            <summary>Docker daemon not running <span class="trouble-symptom">— "Cannot connect to Docker daemon"</span></summary>
            <div class="trouble-body">
              <div class="trouble-label">Cause</div>
              <div class="trouble-note">WSL2's systemd stopped or failed to start <code>docker.service</code>. Common after Windows forced restart or WSL2 crash.</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Fix</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">MSYS_NO_PATHCONV=1 wsl -d Ubuntu-22.04 -u root -- bash -c \
  "systemctl reset-failed docker.service && systemctl start docker.service"</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Verify</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">MSYS_NO_PATHCONV=1 wsl -d Ubuntu-22.04 -u root -- docker info --format '{{.ServerVersion}}'</div>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="trouble">
            <summary>Stack containers stopped <span class="trouble-symptom">— localhost:3456 unreachable</span></summary>
            <div class="trouble-body">
              <div class="trouble-label">Cause</div>
              <div class="trouble-note">Docker daemon restarted but <code>atlas-stack.service</code> didn't bring containers back up. This can happen when the daemon crashes and recovers.</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Fix (slash command)</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">/stack-up</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Fix (manual)</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">MSYS_NO_PATHCONV=1 wsl -d Ubuntu-22.04 -u root -- \
  docker compose -f /mnt/c/Data/Projects/code/Atlas/docker-compose.yml up -d</div>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="trouble">
            <summary>EJS changes not reflected <span class="trouble-symptom">— UI looks unchanged after editing a .ejs file</span></summary>
            <div class="trouble-body">
              <div class="trouble-label">Cause</div>
              <div class="trouble-note"><code>NODE_ENV=production</code> enables EJS's compiled template cache. The old version is served until the process restarts.</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Fix</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">MSYS_NO_PATHCONV=1 wsl -d Ubuntu-22.04 -- docker restart atlas-webapp</div>
              <div class="trouble-note" style="margin-top:8px">Zero-downtime: Express continues serving existing requests during restart. Average restart time is ~3 s.</div>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="trouble">
            <summary>Webapp container stuck "starting" <span class="trouble-symptom">— health check never reaches "healthy"</span></summary>
            <div class="trouble-body">
              <div class="trouble-label">Cause</div>
              <div class="trouble-note">App crashed at startup (syntax error, missing dependency, data file parse error). <code>/api/health</code> never responds so Docker keeps retrying.</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Check logs</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">MSYS_NO_PATHCONV=1 wsl -d Ubuntu-22.04 -- docker logs atlas-webapp --tail 50</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Force restart</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">MSYS_NO_PATHCONV=1 wsl -d Ubuntu-22.04 -- docker restart atlas-webapp</div>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="trouble">
            <summary>atlas-stack.service fails on boot <span class="trouble-symptom">— stack doesn't auto-start after login</span></summary>
            <div class="trouble-body">
              <div class="trouble-label">Cause</div>
              <div class="trouble-note">Docker daemon wasn't ready when the service started, or the service definition is broken. Check the systemd journal for the real error.</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Diagnose</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">MSYS_NO_PATHCONV=1 wsl -d Ubuntu-22.04 -u root -- \
  journalctl -u atlas-stack.service --no-pager -n 30</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Manual start</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">MSYS_NO_PATHCONV=1 wsl -d Ubuntu-22.04 -u root -- \
  systemctl reset-failed atlas-stack.service && systemctl start atlas-stack.service</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Inspect service definition</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">MSYS_NO_PATHCONV=1 wsl -d Ubuntu-22.04 -u root -- \
  cat /etc/systemd/system/atlas-stack.service</div>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="trouble">
            <summary>Price scraper returns "N/A" <span class="trouble-symptom">— product tracked but shows no price</span></summary>
            <div class="trouble-body">
              <div class="trouble-label">Cause</div>
              <div class="trouble-note">The store updated its HTML structure and the Cheerio CSS selector no longer matches the price element. Each store has its own scraper file.</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Locate the scraper</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">tools/price-tracker/scrapers/&lt;store-name&gt;.js</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Run the scraper manually to test</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">cd tools/price-tracker && node index.js check --product &lt;product-id&gt;</div>
              <div class="trouble-note" style="margin-top:8px">Open the store page in DevTools, find the price element, update the CSS selector in the scraper file.</div>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="trouble">
            <summary>Training or health page shows no data <span class="trouble-symptom">— dashboard is empty</span></summary>
            <div class="trouble-body">
              <div class="trouble-label">Cause</div>
              <div class="trouble-note">The data file is missing or has malformed JSON. The server renders an empty array when the file can't be parsed.</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Check file exists</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">data/health/training-plan.json
data/health/fitness-log.json
data/health/sleep-log.json</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Validate JSON</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">MSYS_NO_PATHCONV=1 wsl -d Ubuntu-22.04 -- \
  node -e "JSON.parse(require('fs').readFileSync('/atlas-data/health/training-plan.json','utf8'))"</div>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="trouble">
            <summary>Calendar page shows no events <span class="trouble-symptom">— empty calendar</span></summary>
            <div class="trouble-body">
              <div class="trouble-label">Cause</div>
              <div class="trouble-note">The calendar events cache file is missing or empty. calendar-agent must be run to sync events from Google Calendar.</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Check cache file</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">data/organizer/calendar-events.json</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Re-sync from Google Calendar</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">Ask Atlas: "sync my calendar events for the next 2 weeks"</div>
              <div class="trouble-note" style="margin-top:8px">calendar-agent will authenticate via OAuth if the token is expired and write the events to the cache file.</div>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="trouble">
            <summary>Claude Code hooks not firing <span class="trouble-symptom">— startup context block missing</span></summary>
            <div class="trouble-body">
              <div class="trouble-label">Cause</div>
              <div class="trouble-note">Hook scripts must be executable and the paths in <code>.claude/settings.json</code> must be correct. A non-zero exit from a <code>PreToolUse</code> hook with <code>exit 2</code> blocks the tool call.</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Check hook config</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">.claude/settings.json  →  "hooks" section</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Check startup script is executable</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">MSYS_NO_PATHCONV=1 wsl -d Ubuntu-22.04 -- \
  ls -la /mnt/c/Data/Projects/code/Atlas/hooks/</div>
              <div class="trouble-note" style="margin-top:8px">Exit code 2 = blocks + shows message. Exit code 1 = non-blocking warning. Exit code 0 = success.</div>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="trouble">
            <summary>docker compose changes not taking effect <span class="trouble-symptom">— env vars or volumes unchanged after restart</span></summary>
            <div class="trouble-body">
              <div class="trouble-label">Cause</div>
              <div class="trouble-note">Docker only applies environment variable and volume changes at container creation, not on restart. A plain <code>docker restart</code> reuses the old container config.</div>
              <div class="trouble-label">Fix — force-recreate</div>
              <div class="trouble-cmd">MSYS_NO_PATHCONV=1 wsl -d Ubuntu-22.04 -u root -- \
  docker compose -f /mnt/c/Data/Projects/code/Atlas/docker-compose.yml \
  up -d --force-recreate</div>
            </div>
          </details>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  </div>

</div>

<script>
